This paper deals with type and effect systems, which are a fundamental tool in programming languages and software engineering. The paper presents a proof technique based on reducibility candidates, which is a well-known technique in the field of programming language semantics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also deals with termination analysis, which is a topic in logic and computer science, so cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with multi-threading and interaction mechanisms, which are topics in software engineering, so cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with lambda-calculus, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, so cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories.
